
The hdfs dfsadmin command lets you administer HDFS from the command line.

//general report of the cluster 
hdfs dfsadmin -report
sudo -u hdfs hdfs dfsadmin -metasave test.txt

//print topology of the cluster
hdfs dfsadmin -printTopology
sudo -u hdfs hdfs dfsadmin -printTopology

//updates the NameNode with the list of DataNodes that are allowed to connect to the NameNode.
hdfs dfsadmin â€“refreshNodes



